<% if true %>
<div id="upcoming" class="py-3 text-center">
  <a class="railscamp bg-white text-primary py-1 px-5">rails camp tickets on sale now!</a>
</div>
<% end %>

<div id="mission-statement" class="d-flex">
  <%#
  The founding purpose of Ruby Australia is to further the use and adoption of
  the Ruby programming language in Australia, and to support and encourage a
  vibrant community around the language and related technologies.
  %>
  <div class="pl-5 pr-3 pt-5 pb-5 flex-shrink-0 flex-grow-0">
    <%= image_tag 'ruby_au_logo_new', alt: 'Ruby Australia logo', width: 75, height: 65 %>
  </div>
  <div class="pr-3 pt-5 pb-5 flex-fill">
    <p>RubyAU is a friendly community of coders who meet semi-regularly, have fun,
      learn from each other and refine our craft.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<section id="meetups">
  <h3>Meetups</h3>

  <p>
    There are a number of regional Ruby-related meetups all over the country.
    Each group is organised independently by its members, and all are very
    welcoming to newcomers. The following groups meet regularly:
  </p>

  <ul class="meetup-locations">
    <li>
      <%= link_to "Adelaide", "https://www.meetup.com/adelaiderb/", id: "adl" %>
    </li>
    <li>
      <%= link_to "Brisbane", "https://www.meetup.com/brisRuby/", id: "bne" %>
    </li>
    <li>
      <%= link_to "Canberra", "https://www.meetup.com/canberra-ruby/", id: "can" %>
    </li>
    <li>
      <%= link_to "Melbourne", "https://www.meetup.com/Ruby-On-Rails-Oceania-Melbourne/", id: "mel" %>
    </li>
    <li>
      <%= link_to "Perth", "https://www.meetup.com/roro-perth/", id: "per" %>
    </li>
    <li>
      <%= link_to "Sydney", "https://www.meetup.com/Ruby-On-Rails-Oceania-Sydney/", id: "syd" %>
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section id="railscamp">
  <h3>Rails Camp</h3>

  <p>
    Ruby Australia is the organising body of Australian Rails Camp events.
    Please see the official <%= link_to "Rails Camp", "http://railscamps.com" %>
    site for more details.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="rubyconf-au">
  <h3>RubyConf Australia</h3>
  <p>
    Ruby Australia is the organising body of RubyConf Australia.
    Please see the official
    <%= link_to "RubyConf AU", "http://rubyconf.org.au" %> site for more details.
  </p>
</section>

<section>
  <h3>Contributing to the site</h3>
  <p>
    The site's source is hosted on GitHub:
    <%= link_to "github.com/rubyaustralia/ruby_au",
    "https://github.com/rubyaustralia/ruby_au" %>.
    Please refer to the
    <%= link_to "README", "https://github.com/rubyaustralia/ruby_au#readme" %>
    there for more details,
    or join our slack channel
    <%= link_to "here", "https://ruby-au-join.herokuapp.com/" %>
  </p>
</section>
